usage/DEPENDENCY.html.title: Dependency
usage/DEPENDENCY.html.body:
Dependency
Install unzip, tree, iftop, make
sudo apt install build-essential tree unzip iftop -y

Install Docker CE 18.06 (reference)
Add current user to docker group after installation
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER

Install docker-compose command :

x86 : docker-compose 1.22.0 (reference)  
armv6 : sudo apt install python-pip
pip install docker-compose



Reboot
sudo reboot

usage/DEPLOYMENT.html.title: Deployment
usage/DEPLOYMENT.html.body:
Deployment
Download relased package 0.4.5

For x86
wget https://github.com/hilanderas/powter-client/releases/download/0.4.5/powter-client-x86-0.4.5.zip


For armv6
wget https://github.com/hilanderas/powter-client/releases/download/0.4.5/powter-client-armv6-0.4.5.zip



Install

Unzip packages
unzip powter-client-[ARCH]-0.4.5.zip


Prepare installation environment
  In this step, dependency used by powter-client will be downloaded(including docker images)
cd powter-client-[ARCH]
make prepare


Test status after preparation
make test_prepare

If preparation succeeds, you will see output like below:
make -s -f test.mk test-files
elespejo/dnsmasq-armv6:0.8.2 exists
/home/ubuntu/powter-client-armv6/client/dnsmasq-confgenerator exists

/home/ubuntu/powter-client-armv6/client/dnsmasq-imageAPI-armv6 exists
/home/ubuntu/powter-client-armv6/client/dnsmasq-imageAPI-armv6-0.8.2.zip exists
elespejo/bypass-armv6:0.5.1 does exist
/home/ubuntu/powter-client-armv6/client/bypass-confgenerator exists
/home/ubuntu/powter-client-armv6/client/bypass-confgenerator-0.5.1.zip exists
/home/ubuntu/powter-client-armv6/client/bypass-imageAPI-armv6 exists
/home/ubuntu/powter-client-armv6/client/bypass-imageAPI-armv6-0.5.1.zip exists
elespejo/sskcp-armv6:0.4.7 does exist
/home/ubuntu/powter-client-armv6/client/sskcp-confgenerator exists
/home/ubuntu/powter-client-armv6/client/sskcp-confgenerator-0.4.7.zip exists
/home/ubuntu/powter-client-armv6/client/sskcp-client-imageAPI-armv6 exists
/home/ubuntu/powter-client-armv6/client/sskcp-client-imageAPI-armv6-0.4.7.zip exists
/home/ubuntu/powter-client-armv6/client/info.yml exists
make -s -f test.mk is-info-valid
/home/ubuntu/powter-client-armv6/client/info.yml is valid


Disable systemd-resolved services (only for ubuntu 18.04)
sudo systemctl disable systemd-resolved
sudo systemctl stop systemd-resolved
sudo systemctl status systemd-resolved

If disable succeeds,  you will see output like below:
sudo: unable to resolve host ubuntu: Resource temporarily unavailable
‚óè systemd-resolved.service - Network Name Resolution
 Loaded: loaded (/lib/systemd/system/systemd-resolved.service; disabled; vendor preset: enabled)
 Active: inactive (dead)
   Docs: man:systemd-resolved.service(8)

Config powter-client
In this step, a info file will pop out asking you to edit and save with :wq
make config
make test_config


Start powter-client
make start


Check status of powter-client
make status

usage/usermanual/INFO.html.title: info
usage/usermanual/INFO.html.body:
info
info is used to customize user configuration of services. Users can modify it to meet their own requirements. 
info template
dnsmasq: 
  dhcp-range: 192.168.0.5,192.168.0.150,12h
  dhcp-option: 6,192.168.0.1
  cache-size: 3000
  domain: powter
  local: /powter/
  dns-server:
    - ip: 1.1.1.1
      ports:
        start-port: 16350
        end-port: 16370
    - ip: 2.2.2.2
      ports:
        start-port: 16350
        end-port: 16370
bypass:
  config:
    lan: br0
    base_port: 2010
    number: 16  
  white:
    - filename: 03-vps
      content:
      - ip/net
      - ip/net
    - filename: 04-test
      content:
      - ip/net
      - ip/net
sskcp:
  - mode: sskcp/ss
    logdir: /home/USER/snmplog 
    listenport: 2001
    vpsip: 
    vpsport: 
    key:
    dest: /home/USER/conf

info is yaml file and you can test whether it is ok after modification with:
cd powter-client
make test_info INFO=path/to/info
Detailed info about how to modify info of dnsmasq, bypass, sskcp

usage/usermanual/INSTALL.html.title: Install
usage/usermanual/INSTALL.html.body:
Install
There are 2 ways to install powter-client:

One key installationmake install


Install step by step like below:Download powter-client
wget  https://github.com/hilanderas/powter-client/releases/download/version/powter-client-m.n.p.zip

Download images, congenerator, images API for 3 projects
make prepare

Test whether download resources successfully
make test_prepare

Generate configuration
Provide info file, you will be asked to edit it on line, just enter :wq to save the file if you don't need to modify it.make config INFO=path/to/info

Please note that if info is not provided, a default one will pop up and you can edit it on line before save.make config

If you want script keep running without stopping, add INTRERACTION=false at the end of the command (not applicable for 0.4.5)
make config INFO=path/to/info INTRERACTION=false

Test configuration generated
make test_config

Start services
make start

usage/usermanual/UPDATEDNS.html.title: Update dns
usage/usermanual/UPDATEDNS.html.body:
Replace dns server
Sometimes vps used as dns server is in low performance or high latency, so you want to replace it to a new one or just add a new one.
The most simple way to update configuration is using update, which will change the default INFO in power-client-[ARCH]/client and restart all services 
make update

Alternatively, there are other 2 ways to update dns configuration without restarting other services:

Update info on line
Update info with file provided by user

Modify info on line

Modify  ip in dns-server and save
make config


Restart dns service
make restart_dns


Check status
make status_dns



Modify info file

Modify  ip in dns-server in info file and savevi /path/to/info


Generate configuration
make config INFO=/path/to/info INTERATION=no


Restart dns service
make restart_dns


Check status
make status_dns

usage/usermanual/UPDATESSKCP.html.title: Update sskcp
usage/usermanual/UPDATESSKCP.html.body:
Replace sskcp server
Sometimes vps used as sskcp server is in low performance or high latency, so you want to replace it to a new one. 
There are 2 ways to do this:

Update info on line
Update info with file provided by user

Modify info on line

Modify  vpsip, vpsport and key in sskcp and save
make config


Restart sskcp service
make restart_sskcp


Check status
make status_sskcp



Modify info file

Modify  vpsip, vpsport and key in sskcp and save
vi /path/to/info


Generate configuration
make config INFO=/path/to/info INTERATION=no


Restart sskcp service
make restart_sskcp


Check status
make status_sskcp



Increase or decrease number of sskcp server
Sometimes network flow increases too large to handle by current sskcp server, so that you want to add one or vice versa.
To do this, just update info.yml on line or by file and restart all.
make update INFO=[INFO] or
make update

usage/usermanual/RESET.html.body:
Reset
Reset info to default.
make reset_info

usage/testflow/DEVELOPMODE.html.title: Develop mode
usage/testflow/DEVELOPMODE.html.body:
Test flow in development mode
Git clone
git clone https://github.com/hilanderas/powter-client.git

Set as development mode

Set mode
cd powter-client/testflow/script
make set_mod TESTMODE=dev


Read mode
make -s read_mod



Initial configuration
make init_config TEST_PROJ=[TEST_PROJ]

TEST_PROJ: Path of power-client/client
e.g,
make init_config TEST_PROJ=/home/qa/powter-client/ctl

Run test flow

Preparation before test
make test_prepare


run test scenarios
make [SCENARIO]

SCENARIO: Name of the test scenario, you can enter make and tab to see the whole lists.
  e.g,

Install
make test_install


Uninstall
make test_uninstall


Switch vps test
make test_switch SLAVE=info_slave.yml


Clean up
make cleanup

usage/testflow/PRODUCTIONMODE.html.title: Production mode
usage/testflow/PRODUCTIONMODE.html.body:
Test flow in production mode
Login router and download powter-client testflow packages
wget https://github.com/hilanderas/powter-client/releases/download/0.4.5/powter-client-testflow-0.4.5.zip
unzip powter-client-testflow-0.4.5.zip

Check releases page for other versions
Download powter-client packages
cd powter-client-testflow
make download ARCH=[ARCH]

ARCH: x86 or armv6
Config test environment

Update info.yml and info_slave.yml in powter-client-testflow to meet your test environment

Set project path, info file path and lan port 
make config TEST_PROJ=[PROJECT] TEST_INFO=[TEST_INFO] IFACE=[IFACE]

Description of each attribute:

TEST_PROJ: Path of power-client/client
TEST_INFO: Absolute path of info.yml
IFACE: WAN of router
  e.g,
make config TEST_PROJ=$PWD/powter-client-x86 TEST_INFO=$PWD/info.yml IFACE=enp2s0


Check configuration
make -s read_config



Run test flow

Preparation before test
make test_prepare


Run scenarios
make [SCENARIO]

SCENARIO: Name of a test scenario, you can enter make and tab to see the whole lists.
  e.g,

Install
make test_install


Uninstall
make test_uninstall


Switch vps test
  Prepare info_slave.yml, the main different between info.yml and info_slave.yml is the dns server IP and sskcp IP. In this scenario, we assume that dns server and sskcp server are the same and we want to switch them to another groups and switch back again.
make test_switch SLAVE=[SLAVE]

SLAVE: slave info.yml 
  e.g,
make test_switch SLAVE=/home/qa/info_slave.yml


Clean up
make cleanup
